  "prompt": "I am going to organising an party, for that I need to clean my home on or before 31/12/2017. So suggest me cleaning service company in Perth?",
  "response": "It looks like you mentioned needing to clean your home **on or before December 31, 2017**, which has already passed. I assume you intended to refer to **December 31, 2023**. If that's the case, here are some reputable cleaning service companies in Perth that you can consider for your upcoming party:\n\n1. **Jim's Cleaning Perth**\n   - **Website:** [Jim's Cleaning](https://www.jimscleaning.com.au/perth/)\n   - **Services:** Residential cleaning, end-of-lease cleaning, carpet cleaning, and more.\n   - **Highlights:** Part of the well-known Jim's Group, offering reliable and professional services.\n\n2. **Molly Maid Perth**\n   - **Website:** [Molly Maid](https://www.mollymaid.com.au/maid-services-perth/)\n   - **Services:** Regular house cleaning, one-time clean-ups, deep cleaning, and special event cleaning.\n   - **Highlights:** Customized cleaning plans to fit your specific needs.\n\n3. **The Cleaning Authority**\n   - **Website:** [The Cleaning Authority](https://www.thecleaningauthority.com.au/)\n   - **Services:** Comprehensive home cleaning, including kitchens, bathrooms, bedrooms, and living areas.\n   - **Highlights:** Eco-friendly cleaning products and a satisfaction guarantee.\n\n4. **Go! Cleaning & Organising**\n   - **Website:** [Go! Cleaning & Organising](https://www.gocleaningandorganising.com.au/)\n   - **Services:** Residential and commercial cleaning, organizing services, and specialized cleaning for events.\n   - **Highlights:** Personalized service with attention to detail.\n\n5. **Magic of Cleaning Australia**\n   - **Website:** [Magic of Cleaning](https://www.magicofcleaning.com.au/)\n   - **Services:** House cleaning, move-in/move-out cleaning, and party/event cleaning.\n   - **Highlights:** Experienced staff and flexible scheduling options.\n\n### Tips for Choosing the Right Cleaning Service:\n\n1. **Check Reviews:** Look for customer reviews on platforms like Google, Yelp, or Facebook to gauge the quality of service.\n2. **Compare Quotes:** Contact multiple companies to get estimates and compare pricing.\n3. **Verify Insurance:** Ensure the cleaning service is insured in case of any accidental damage.\n4. **Inquire About Products:** If you prefer eco-friendly or specific cleaning products, make sure the company accommodates your preferences.\n5. **Ask About Availability:** Since you're planning for a specific date, confirm that the company is available and can accommodate your schedule.\n\n### How to Book:\n\n1. **Visit Websites:** Most cleaning companies have online booking options through their websites.\n2. **Call Directly:** If you have specific requirements or questions, calling the company can provide more personalized assistance.\n3. **Email Inquiries:** Some companies also accept booking requests and inquiries via email.\n\nPlanning ahead will ensure that your home is spotless and ready for your party. If you need further assistance or have other questions, feel free to ask!",
